The order to quarantine the lawmakers was made by Director of Health Services Malaki Tshipayagae, according to a tweet from the government. The country's on Thursday confirmed seven new coronavirus cases, including a health worker who was on duty during parliament's session on Wednesday. President Mokgweetsi Masisi also attended the session in which lawmakers debated on extending the state of emergency to to six months. The President recently concluded his 14 days in quarantine after he returned from Namibia in March. Botswana now has a total of 13 confirmed coronavirus cases. The country is on a 28-day lockdown to prevent the spread of the virus. --BBC--